--- !u!114 &664294340
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 664294338}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 635b5bdfdff1bd247a7879b0b6fc2618, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  devNote: 'You can move the positions of the children of this game object, then
    when you press "Move" you''ll see how the ball moves a different path.

    Pressing
    show model will show a model whose right leg is controlled using inverse kinematics
    to target the same position as the ball. This is to visualise how you can use
    bezier curves and inverse kinematics to make procedural animations. By placing
    P_3 and P_2 higher up, it can create an animation of the model walking upwards.

    By
    placing P_1 and P_2 in the same place left of P_0, then placing P_3 to the right,
    it can create an animation of the model kicking.'
